45:14.746 --> 45:17.010
Are you prepared to do
a broadcast right now?

45:17.082 --> 45:18.709
Yeah.

45:18.784 --> 45:21.344
The camera guy.

45:21.420 --> 45:22.683
What about him?

45:22.754 --> 45:24.222
Is Jerome.

45:24.289 --> 45:26.383
Jerome is the camera
operator on number two.

45:26.458 --> 45:27.948
[Snaps fingers]
And he likes hockey.

45:28.026 --> 45:29.323
Now you're with it.

45:29.394 --> 45:31.123
<i>Will: 60 seconds to VTR,</i>

45:31.196 --> 45:32.129
<i>two minutes live.</i>

45:32.197 --> 45:33.722
All right, here's a change.

45:33.799 --> 45:36.825
We're flip-flopping the Virginia Slims
quarterfinals and the IOC meeting.

45:36.902 --> 45:38.392
-- Kill <i>23.</i>
-- <i>I never had 23.</i>

45:38.470 --> 45:40.097
Then you won't miss it much.

45:40.172 --> 45:41.936
Jeremy, tell me what's
happening in Chattanooga.

45:42.007 --> 45:44.032
Tell me quickly. Tell me
succinctly -- bullet points.

45:44.109 --> 45:46.373
[Snaps fingers] We're on the
air in less than two minutes,

45:46.445 --> 45:47.913
so don't give me
a Valedictory address.

45:47.980 --> 45:50.108
Talk to me as if
I'm a small child.

45:50.182 --> 45:52.583
Tell me what's happening
in Chattanooga.

45:52.651 --> 45:54.642
I don't know what's
happening in Chattanooga.

45:54.720 --> 45:57.553
Okay, tell me
a little more than that.

45:57.622 --> 45:59.522
I think, as a
New Year's resolution,

45:59.591 --> 46:02.322
you should re-dedicate yourself
to the idea that this is a team.

46:02.394 --> 46:04.556
You play for a team --
a team with many players.

46:04.629 --> 46:06.757
-- And you think I should learn their
names. -- <i>I</i> think it'd be nice.

46:06.832 --> 46:09.028
-- I agree. -- See, a team's made
<i>up</i> of a <i>group</i> of individuals...

46:09.101 --> 46:11.035
-- <i>You're gonna keep talking anyway?</i>
-- <i>Individuals who forsake</i>

46:11.103 --> 46:13.538
their own individual needs
to pursue a common goal --

46:13.605 --> 46:15.039
the team goal.

46:15.107 --> 46:17.235
In our case, the goal is a nightly
national television show.

46:17.309 --> 46:19.243
I'm saying I know
the guy's name now.

46:19.311 --> 46:21.211
<i>Will: Roll VTR.
60 seconds, live.</i>

46:21.279 --> 46:23.577
Show me Tokyo.
Show me the Chyron on 4.

46:23.648 --> 46:25.377
-- 4 is up.
-- You've got Tokyo.

46:25.450 --> 46:26.781
That was Brian
in Chattanooga.

46:26.852 --> 46:28.547
All right, tell me what he
knows -- bullet points.

46:28.620 --> 46:30.611
I can feed it right to Casey
and put it in the tease.

46:30.689 --> 46:33.056
Casey, stand by, I'm gonna fill the tease.
What does he know?

46:33.125 --> 46:35.856
-- He doesn't know anything.
-- Stop standing by, Casey.

46:35.927 --> 46:37.019
What's going on?

46:37.095 --> 46:38.529
<i>There was an incident
at Tennessee Western</i>

46:38.597 --> 46:41.032
involving some black athletes
and a Confederate flag.

46:41.099 --> 46:43.090
-- What happened?
-- We <i>don't know.</i>

46:43.168 --> 46:45.034
<i>Dave." In 3...2...</i>

46:45.103 --> 46:47.197
Good evening.
From New York City,

46:47.272 --> 46:49.764
I'm Casey McCall
alongside Dan Rydell.

46:49.841 --> 46:52.276
Those stories, plus we'll
head out to the Hoosier Dome

46:52.344 --> 46:54.836
where Bobby Knight's done a
little interior decorating,

46:54.913 --> 46:56.506
and we'll leave room
for more hockey

46:56.581 --> 46:58.140
than you can shake
a big stick at.

46:58.216 --> 47:00.844
We'll bring you the thrill of
victory and the agony of defeat

47:00.919 --> 47:03.217
and, because we've got
soccer highlights,

47:03.288 --> 47:06.258
the sheer pointlessness
of a zero-zero tie.

47:06.324 --> 47:08.622
You're watching “Sports Night“
on CSC, so stick around.

47:08.693 --> 47:10.161
<i>We're out.</i>

47:10.228 --> 47:11.320
Back in 60.

47:11.396 --> 47:13.296
What's going on
in Chattanooga?

47:13.365 --> 47:14.332
We don't know.

47:14.399 --> 47:16.060
-- We don't know?
-- We don't know.

47:16.134 --> 47:18.466
-- We don't know anything?
-- We don't know much.

47:18.537 --> 47:21.097
But, fundamentally, we're still a
news-gathering organization, right?

47:21.173 --> 47:22.163
Sure.

47:22.240 --> 47:24.265
-- Then what's the problem?
-- We're not very good.

47:24.342 --> 47:26.640
That's what I thought.

47:30.682 --> 47:32.411
Comin' back on Dan
in 3...2...

47:32.484 --> 47:35.010
<i>Woman: Dan, Casey,
back to you in the studio.</i>

47:35.087 --> 47:37.351
Thank you, Kelly Kirkpatrick,
in Green Bay.

47:37.422 --> 47:39.356
You look cold.
Put some clothes on.

47:39.424 --> 47:41.324
Hey, folks, look outside.

47:41.393 --> 47:42.758
Tinsel, mistletoe...

47:42.828 --> 47:44.922
It can only mean
one thing.

47:44.996 --> 47:46.020
Casey.

47:46.098 --> 47:47.691
<i>Play of the year.</i>

47:47.766 --> 47:49.359
<i>Play 0' the year.</i>

47:49.434 --> 47:52.028
Our crack staff has been
debating the subject,

47:52.104 --> 47:54.004
and we'll bring you our
choice on New Year's Eve,

47:54.072 --> 47:55.130
but we want to hear from you,

47:55.207 --> 47:56.675
so if you've
got a play of the year,

47:56.741 --> 48:00.177
you can contact us at
CSC/sportsnighLcom,

48:00.245 --> 48:03.271
or just go on over to Casey's apartment
and knock on the door anytime.

48:03.348 --> 48:05.680
That's all for us. You've been
watching “Sports Night“ on CSC.

48:05.750 --> 48:07.047
We'll see you tomorrow.

48:07.119 --> 48:08.109
Good night.

48:08.186 --> 48:09.347
-- Music.
-- Go.

48:09.421 --> 48:10.582
-- Animation.
-- Go.

48:10.655 --> 48:12.623
