Wolfgang Puck! You want a piece of me?

48:33.945 --> 48:35.413
No, but thanks.

48:35.480 --> 48:37.915
You know, it wouldn't kill you to
go out there and do a little press.

48:37.983 --> 48:39.212
I've been grounded,
remember?

48:39.284 --> 48:41.218
How long's the network
got you in the penalty box?

48:41.286 --> 48:42.754
No public statements
for six months.

48:42.821 --> 48:44.380
-- You want me to talk to somebody?
-- No.

48:44.456 --> 48:45.582
-- I can.
-- I'm perfectly happy

48:45.657 --> 48:47.989
just doing my job
and keeping my mouth shut.

48:48.059 --> 48:49.857
I don't need
to give interviews.

48:49.928 --> 48:51.362
I don't even want to
give interviews.

48:51.429 --> 48:53.227
I'm happy for the chance
to not give interviews.

48:53.298 --> 48:55.232
-- You don't want me to talk to 'em?
-- No.

48:55.300 --> 48:56.893
-- Okay.
-- Talk to 'em.

48:56.968 --> 48:59.403
-- Danny... -- I need to give interviews.
I like to give interviews.

48:59.471 --> 49:02.406
It's the only chance I get to talk
to a huge group of total strangers.

49:02.474 --> 49:04.670
-- Except for that hour every night
you're on television. -- That's right.

49:04.743 --> 49:06.074
-- I'll talk to 'em.
Dana: Hey.

49:06.144 --> 49:08.169
-- Knock 'em dead on the cooking
show tomorrow. -- Thank you.

49:08.246 --> 49:09.236
[Laughs]

49:09.314 --> 49:11.305
[Cheers and applause]

49:13.518 --> 49:14.952
And welcome back
to "The View."

49:15.020 --> 49:16.545
We are talking with
Casey McCall,

49:16.621 --> 49:17.952
<i>co-host of "Sports Night,"</i>

49:18.023 --> 49:21.118
which can be seen every night
at 11:00 P.M. on CSC.

49:21.193 --> 49:23.890
Yes, with my partner, Dan Rydell,
who couldn't be here this morning.

49:23.962 --> 49:25.327
Hope he has a good excuse.

49:25.397 --> 49:28.162
-- Yes, uh, he likes to sleep late.
-- Good enough.

49:28.233 --> 49:31.100
Before we went to commercial, you were
saying that you and, uh, Dan write together.

49:31.169 --> 49:32.136
<i>Yes.</i>

49:32.204 --> 49:33.330
How does that work?

49:33.405 --> 49:34.895
Well, I take
the nouns and verbs.

49:34.973 --> 49:36.771
Danny handles the adjectives
and prepositions,

49:36.841 --> 49:39.310
and, uh, anything with
an umlaut, we toss a coin.

49:39.377 --> 49:41.209
<i>Now, Casey, you know
we can't let you go</i>

49:41.279 --> 49:42.940
without asking you
about those ties.

49:43.014 --> 49:44.914
Ah, the ties.

49:44.983 --> 49:46.576
<i>The famous neckties.</i>

49:46.651 --> 49:48.551
<i>Now, listen up, ladies.
You're single, right?</i>

49:48.620 --> 49:51.089
-- Yes, I'm recently divorced. --
I/VeH, <i>I</i> think you should know

49:51.156 --> 49:54.182
that a man who knows how to dress
himself is a very sexy thing.

49:54.259 --> 49:57.092
Which is why so many of
us are drawn to Carrot Top.

49:57.162 --> 49:58.527
<i>Debbie: Absolutely.</i>

49:58.597 --> 50:00.224
<i>All right, if you're
a sports fan</i>

50:00.298 --> 50:02.733
or just like neckties,
don't miss "Sports Night"

50:02.801 --> 50:05.065
with Dan Rydell and our
guest, Casey McCall,

50:05.136 --> 50:07.298
every night at 11:00 on CSC.

50:07.372 --> 50:09.101
We'll be right back
after this.

50:09.174 --> 50:12.269
[Cheers and applause] Thank you.
Thank you very much.

50:17.382 --> 50:19.646
<i>By the way, in the memos
that are circulating,</i>

50:19.718 --> 50:22.187
we're spelling Chattanooga
about 14 different ways.

50:22.254 --> 50:23.346
Now what do we know?

50:23.421 --> 50:24.820
Two O's, three A's.

50:24.889 --> 50:26.880
-- <i>That's it?</i> -- <i>No, there
are other letters, too.</i>

50:27.892 --> 50:30.827
-- But surely that's not
what you meant. -- No.

50:30.895 --> 50:32.385
Roland Shepard is a tailback

50:32.464 --> 50:34.796
from a small town in western
Tennessee called Tipolo --

50:34.866 --> 50:35.992
one one

50:36.067 --> 50:37.535
He rode the bench
for two years,

50:37.602 --> 50:39.661
and then two weeks ago,
he won the starting job

50:39.738 --> 50:41.706
<i>when Lfffias went down
with</i> a <i>torn AOL.</i>

