52:21.506 --> 52:23.531
-- <i>Then don't.</i>
-- <i>There are days, Danny,</i>

52:23.608 --> 52:26.100
-- when I'm just too tired to fight
that man. -- You gotta let <i>us</i> know

52:26.177 --> 52:27.702
when it's one of those days,
and we'll fight him for you.

52:27.779 --> 52:29.543
You gotta stop
thinking of me

52:29.614 --> 52:31.981
as the champion
of all things black.

52:37.922 --> 52:39.720
Now, listen up, ladies.
You're single, right?

52:39.791 --> 52:42.089
-- Yes, I'm recently divorced. --
I/VeH, <i>I</i> think you should know

52:42.160 --> 52:45.186
that a man who knows how to dress
himself is a very sexy thing.

52:45.263 --> 52:47.425
<i>Which is why so many of
us are drawn to Carrot Top.</i>

52:47.499 --> 52:49.092
<i>Debbie: Absolutely.</i>

52:49.167 --> 52:51.135
<i>[Knock on door] AH right, if
you're</i> a <i>sports fan or</i> --

52:51.202 --> 52:53.102
-- Excuse me, Mr. McCall?
-- Yeah?

52:53.171 --> 52:55.196
I'm sorry.
Is this a bad time?

52:55.273 --> 52:56.968
-- <i>For</i> what? -- <i>I'd like
to ask you</i> a <i>question,</i>

52:57.041 --> 52:58.440
but if you're preparing
the show,

52:58.510 --> 53:00.444
if this is a bad time,
I can -- I can come back.

53:00.512 --> 53:01.673
What's your question?

53:03.348 --> 53:07.148
Well, uh...
what's my name?

53:07.218 --> 53:09.186
