53:09.254 --> 53:10.517
Yes.

53:10.588 --> 53:12.488
Um...

53:12.557 --> 53:14.047
what are we doing
right now?

53:14.125 --> 53:16.184
If this is a bad time,
I can just come --

53:16.261 --> 53:18.787
I'm sorry. I'm not very
good at remembering names.

53:18.863 --> 53:20.331
<i>Who was the number-two man</i>

53:20.398 --> 53:24.130
on the Boston Red Sox
staff in 1977?

53:24.202 --> 53:27.194
It was Ferguson Jenkins.

53:29.474 --> 53:30.999
My name is Monica.

53:31.075 --> 53:34.101
I'm the assistant wardrobe
supervisor for “Sports Night“

53:34.179 --> 53:36.238
as well as two other
shows here at CSC.

53:36.314 --> 53:39.249
I think you hurt the feelings
of the woman I work for.

53:39.317 --> 53:41.479
Her name is Maureen,

53:41.553 --> 53:44.079
and she's been working here
since the day you started.

53:46.658 --> 53:48.092
Well, I know Maureen.

53:48.159 --> 53:49.593
Can I ask you
a-another question?

53:49.694 --> 53:51.685
I'm sorry I didn't
know your name.

53:51.729 --> 53:55.688
-- Do you know what color this is?
-- I/VeH, <i>it's</i> gray.

53:55.767 --> 53:56.996
It's called gunmetal.

53:57.068 --> 53:59.935
